  "content": "Education Minister issues four-point instruction to CTEVT\nRastriya Samachar Samiti (RSS)\nFriday, September 26, 2025\n0\nComments\nFile\nKathmandu, September 26\nMinister for Education, Science and Technology Mahabir Pun issued four-point instructions to the Centre for Technical Education and Vocational Training (CTEVT) for immediate implementation. Minster Pun, also the chair of\nCTEVT,\ninstructed the CTEVT to prepare a framework aiming to improve the existing curriculum and incorporate innovations, and submit it by October 17.\nThe minster also instructed to set ip an integrated calendar and ensure that exam results are published mandatorily within three months. A mechanism that listens to the complaints of students, parents, and teachers at the council’s office, and records/addresses the received complaints must be established and put into operation immediately, stated in the instruction.\nLikewise, a report on all applications received for affiliation since the year 2069 BS should be prepared and submitted to the ministry by October 17, and decisions regarding granting or not granting affiliation should be taken promptly.\nReact to this post\nHot Topics\nmonsoon\nKumari\nRastriya Samachar Samiti (RSS)\nRSS is a government-run national news portal of Nepal.\nMore From the Author\nConversation\nNew\nOld\nPopular\nAdd Comment\nLogin to comment\nRemenber me\nForgot password?\nLogin\nNot have account yet?\nSignup Now\nOr use Social Media?\nGoogle\nFacebook\nTwitter\nForgot Password?\nSend Password Reset Link\nBack\nRelated News\nMonsoon triggers flood and landslide risks in several districts, DHM issues special alert\n59 minutes ago\nLiving Goddess Kumari to offer Dashain Tika to public today\n1 hour ago\nNepalis celebrate Bijaya Dashami, auspicious Tika time set at 11:53 am\n1 hour ago\nKushal Bhurtel shines as player of the series in Unity Cup\n24 hours ago\nMore than 5.5 lakh people exit Valley for Dashain\n24 hours ago\nClay and culture: The making of Durga idols\n24 hours ago\nMost Read\nVarious ways you can enjoy goat meat this Dashain festival\nNepal’s Gen Z movement captures French media and inspires protesters\nFinance Ministry launches digital approval system\nIntellectual Council urges Oli to hand over UML leadership via central committee\nMisleading news affects mental health, ways to cope\nSubscribe to our newsletter\nSubscribe to Onlinekhabar English to get notified of exclusive news stories.\nEditor's Pick\nEditor's Pick\n4 government buildings, including Supreme Court, declared unfit for use\n2 weeks ago\nEditor's Pick\nCharred body found at Koteshwor Bhatbhateni, Gen-Z protest death toll rises to 74\n2 weeks ago\nEditor's Pick\nNo consensus on Hami Nepal’s claim of leading the Gen-Z movement\n2 weeks ago\nEditor's Pick\nDecades-old irrigation projects stall as Madhesh faces drought, food crisis looms\n2 months ago\nEditor's Pick\nNepal’s farming crisis: When plans stay on paper and fields suffer\n2 months ago\nAlso Read\nSociety\nMonsoon triggers flood and landslide risks in several districts, DHM issues special alert\n60 minutes ago\nFestival\nLiving Goddess Kumari to offer Dashain Tika to public today\n1 hour ago\nFestival\nNepalis celebrate Bijaya Dashami, auspicious Tika time set at 11:53 am\n1 hour ago\nBlog\nClay and culture: The making of Durga idols\n24 hours ago\nFestival\nTaleju Temple welcomes devotees on Maha Nawami\n1 day ago",
